commentary: Jadeja to Pietersen, 1 run Trott should've been run out! This could be a costly miss from India. There was total confusion between Pietersen and Trott after the former had nudged into the leg side. Pietersen set off for the single straight away but Trott was nowhere. But the return throw to the keeper was atrocious, and though Dhoni dived to stop it, his shy also went wide!

commentary: Bresnan to Patel, OUT Bresnan strikes! There's not been a great deal of swing out there this evening, but this one swung back in to the left-hander through the air, striking Parthiv on the pad as he poked from the crease.
